  "directive_events": [
    {
      "at": "2026-06-27T15:57:28.744784Z",
      "owner_directive": "Public surface spans more than blocks.base+process: expose other scistudio.blocks types too, and core types to block authors. Package-author surface must expose as much as possible \u2014 previewer + type + block protocols (owner has a template repo to reference). Decisions: (1) declare public surface via __all__, NOT a separate sdk/api re-export module (avoids churning all templates/packages); (2) stability via decorators that the doc generator auto-renders; (3) include the plot render(collection) contract in the ADR as one documented usage.",
      "reason": "Owner refined ADR scope and key design decisions during live discussion"
    },
    {
      "at": "2026-06-27T16:09:29.666454Z",
      "owner_directive": "Agree with decision A (curated root modules = public; deep paths = internal, non-breaking). Doubt that the package _support helpers are truly generic \u2014 ADR must NOT mandate moving them into core; treat core promotion as case-by-case, evidence-gated. The ADR must ALSO specify the package-side public API contract (how a package declares its own public types/blocks/previewers/helpers, no underscore author-facing helpers, package stability/Since, package-side docs). Reference repos: scistudio-package-template, scistudio-blocks-spectroscopy, scistudio-blocks-imaging.",
      "reason": "Owner refined ADR content: confirm decision A (root modules canonical), do NOT presume core absorption of package helpers (genericity unproven), and the ADR must also govern each package's OWN public API contract; imaging repo added as reference"
    },
    {
      "at": "2026-06-27T16:59:46.005031Z",
      "owner_directive": "Add ergonomic accessors to core types because ordinary/custom-block authors know pandas, not Arrow; each package defining its own to_pandas is unacceptable, so it belongs in core once. Constraint: accessors are public-only \u2014 core internal data flow must not use them; canonical to_memory()/Arrow/ndarray unchanged. Exception: planned Excel loader (#1810) must use pandas internally because pyarrow can't read Excel.",
      "reason": "Owner decided: add public-only ergonomic accessors (to_pandas/to_numpy) on core types, inherited by packages, barred from internal data flow (Excel loader #1810 the sole exception)"
    }
  ],
